 the 1600 rez i play on that's making it hard for me i dunno. i havent seen anyone else complaining about it.<br><br>if it's an xml change can anyone point me in the right direction? or at least to the file i should look at?  oddly enough this is the only thing from the standard skin i really really want changed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugeddine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Geddine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/8/02 3:15:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: xp color bar change?</span><hr size=1> Goto your EQUI_InventoryWnd file look for the gauge which shows your XP (something in the lines of IW_XPGauge, not sure don't have it in front of me)<br><br>You'll notice a 2 tags with 3 lines &lt;R&gt;, &lt;G&gt; and &lt;B&gt; in it.  Change the first one to modify the orange.  The second one makes up the blue line (calles LinesFillColor if I remember right).  The only thing about this is even though the variables are there they can still be hard coded into the client, meaning unchangeable, but you wont know until you try it.<br><br>Sorry about the vagueness just at work writing this off the top of my head. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwinterwindmorninglight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Winterwind MorningLight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/8/02 9:40:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: xp color bar change?</span><hr size=1> Here is a color chart for you:<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/colorwizard/colorchart.asp">eq.castersrealm.com/color...rchart.asp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br><br>These bars are all a combination of<br><br>Red<br>Green<br>Blue<br><br><br>Some changes I made to Winter's UI were:<br><br>HP, group hp, and target are now a softer warmer red with touch of blue:<br><br>R  240<br>G  0<br>B  20<br><br>Pretty turquoise (thanks Boanerges!) for Mana:<br><br>R  0<br>G  153<br>B  220<br><br>Nice easy on the eyes green for Stamina bar:<br><br>R  34<br>G  149<br>B  34<br><br><br>Exp bar I left the same:<br><br>R  220<br>G  150<br>B  0<br><br>Bar underlining exp bar is turquoise blue:<br><br>R  0<br>G  110<br>B  180<br><br>AA Exp bar is a pretty darker turquoise:<br><br>R  0<br>G  80<br>B  150<br><br>Pretty Purple underlining bar (might be too dark for you):<br><br>R  60<br>G  0<br>B  126<br><br>I put these on a navy/blue background and they show up really nicely.  The purple may be a little dark to see though.<br><br>Navy/blue background for all my windows (Right click on window to chose TINT option):<br><br>R  30<br>G  0<br>B  132<br><br><br>I'll probably end up posting the UI when I'm finished. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Winterwind MorningLight<br>56th Druid of Tunare<br>Cazic Thule Server<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm41.showPrevMessage?topicID=231.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm41.showNextMessage?topicID=231.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self 